  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance Progamme (HAP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan is one of the most multi-hazard prone countries in South Asia, with earthquakes, floods, droughts, landslides, sandstorms, and avalanches being the most common natural disasters. In addition, conflict intensified throughout the last two quarters of 2020 and the situation is expected to continue to deteriorate following the end of winter around March. The objective of the project is to continue supporting IOM Afghanistan&apos;s Humanitarian Assistance Program (HAP), implementing modifications to enhance its impact and consolidate the gains of the last ten years. The project provides emergency relief assistance through provision of non-food items (NFIs), emergency shelter and cash assistance for vulnerable natural disaster or conflict affected/displaced populations. The project also provides enhanced community level preparedness and capacities by conducting community-based disaster risk management activities in selected disaster-prone communities.  Lastly the project is strengthening the institutional capacity of the Afghanistan National Disaster Management Authority (ANDMA) and providing technical support to provincial ANDMA offices and strengthening of the Emergency Shelter Cluster through dedicated staffing at the national and regional levels.</narrative>
  </description>
